model

Class Importer

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Importer

  • public class Importer
extends java.lang.Object
    The importer class takes care of importing measurement data. Depending on the directory structure and filename it deduces what is an experiment, a sample, a field of view or a file. The level of a directory determines if it refers to an experiment, sample or field of view. For each file the channel is determined by its filename. Channels are (by default) determined by the following conditions:
    acquisition
    filename ends in 'acquisition.tif'
    bright field
    filename ends in 'bf.tif'
    red channel
    filename ends in '568.tif'
    green channel
    filename ends '514.tif'
    blue channel
    filename ends '488.tif'
    Note that after 'bf', '568' and the other channels there might be an extra character. For example: '001 5682.tif'. The '2' indicates that it is the seconds part of the 568 image file.
    Author:
    C.M. Punter

      • importExperiment

        public void importExperiment(java.io.File folder,
                             boolean isTimeSampling)
        For a given root (node) and folder this method will import experiments. You also need to specify if this experiment is time lapse or time sampling.
        Parameters:
        root - the root node
        folder - the folder from which all samples are imported
        isTimeSampling - determines if this experiment is time lapse or not
